primary.context: Caller was having trouble logging into the portal with an invalid account number error
primary.detail: The agent verified the caller and sent a payment link via email and text after the caller confirmed the portal registration link previously sent did not work.

steps: Caller states they cannot get into their account and provides name.
Agent performs account lookup via phone number and verifies identity.
Caller explains the account number is showing as invalid on the portal.
Agent offers a new registration link, but caller states they already tried that and it failed.
Caller clarifies they want to make a payment.
Agent confirms property and contact details, then sends a payment link via text and email.

corrections.note: Caller clarifies previous registration link already failed

insights.summary: The caller wanted to make a payment because they were unable to log into the owner portal. The agent successfully verified the account and sent a payment link via text and email.
insights.verbatim: I'm trying to get into my account. The account number is wrong.
